        <h3>2.1 Sales and Net Sales Module</h3>
        <table class="use-case-table">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td>Use Case ID</td>
                <td>UC-001</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Use Case Name</td>
                <td>Calculate Sales and Net Sales</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Primary Actor</td>
                <td>System (Automated)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pre-Conditions</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>SAP system is available and accessible</li>
                        <li>Sales data has been posted in SAP</li>
                        <li>Invoice-level data is complete</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Basic Process Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>System retrieves sales data from SAP daily</li>
                        <li>System captures Domestic Sales (quantity and value)</li>
                        <li>System captures Export Sales (quantity and value)</li>
                        <li>System captures Waste Sales and Others using waste codes</li>
                        <li>System adjusts for Sales Returns on actual return date</li>
                        <li>System fetches Dealer Commission at invoice level</li>
                        <li>System calculates Price/Rate Differences per SKU</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Distribution Expenses (Outward Freight, Ocean Freight, Commission, Cash Discount, Rate Discount, Internal Freight, Warehouse Charges)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Total Sales = (Sales Value Domestic + Sales Value Export) - Sales Returns Value - Dealer Commission ± Price/Rate Differences</li>
                        <li>System calculates Net Sales = Total Sales - Sales Distribution Expenses</li>
                        <li>System stores results with date and SKU mapping</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Alternate Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If SAP data is unavailable</li>
                        <li>System logs error</li>
                        <li>System sends notification to administrator</li>
                        <li>System uses last available data with warning flag</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Acceptance Criteria</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Sales data is retrieved from SAP daily without manual intervention</li>
                        <li>All SKUs have sales values mapped correctly</li>
                        <li>Distribution expenses are allocated to correct SKUs</li>
                        <li>Net Sales calculation matches formula specification</li>
                        <li>Data is available for reporting within 2 hours of SAP posting</li>
                        <li>Drill-down capability available by SKU, product, date, and plant</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody></table>

        <h3>2.2 Melt (PTA &amp; MEG) Module</h3>
        <table class="use-case-table">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td>Use Case ID</td>
                <td>UC-002</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Use Case Name</td>
                <td>Calculate Melt Cost and Gross Margin</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Primary Actor</td>
                <td>System (Automated) / Finance User (Manual Rate Entry)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pre-Conditions</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>BOM (Bill of Materials) is configured in system</li>
                        <li>Daily production plan is available</li>
                        <li>PTA/MEG rates are entered or available</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Basic Process Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>System retrieves daily production output by SKU</li>
                        <li>System fetches BOM consumption factor for each SKU</li>
                        <li>System calculates PTA/MEG consumption = SKU Output × BOM Factor</li>
                        <li>System uses last manual entry of PTA rate for daily costing</li>
                        <li>Finance User updates PTA/MEG rates as needed</li>
                        <li>At month-end, system adjusts with actual procurement rates</li>
                        <li>System calculates Melt Cost = PTA Consumption × PTA Rate + MEG Consumption × MEG Rate</li>
                        <li>System includes Other Raw Materials cost and Conversion cost</li>
                        <li>System calculates Gross Margin = Net Sales - Melt Cost</li>
                        <li>System stores results with SKU and date mapping</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Alternate Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If BOM is not configured for a SKU</li>
                        <li>System flags error</li>
                        <li>System notifies administrator</li>
                        <li>User must configure BOM before calculation proceeds</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Acceptance Criteria</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>BOM-based consumption mapping works for all SKUs</li>
                        <li>Manual rate entry interface is user-friendly</li>
                        <li>System maintains rate history</li>
                        <li>Gross Margin calculation is accurate</li>
                        <li>Month-end adjustment process works correctly</li>
                        <li>Impact of raw material volatility is tracked</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody></table>

        <h3>2.3 Variable Cost Contribution (VCC) Module</h3>
        <table class="use-case-table">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td>Use Case ID</td>
                <td>UC-003</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Use Case Name</td>
                <td>Calculate Variable Costs and Contribution</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Primary Actor</td>
                <td>System (Automated)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pre-Conditions</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Production data is available</li>
                        <li>Material master rates are updated in SAP</li>
                        <li>Plant-wise correction factors are configured</li>
                        <li>Merge factors are defined</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Basic Process Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>System calculates Power Cost (retrieves plant and production line data, applies rate and quantity norms, multiplies with plant-wise correction factors)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Heating Cost (applies Merge Factor per SKU, calculates required heating quantity, costs at latest manual rate)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Antimony, Additives, Chemicals cost (retrieves quantity from BOM/production plans, fetches rates from SAP material master, calculates cost per SKU)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Packing Material cost (uses BOM and production data, applies rates from material master)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Procured RM - Chips &amp; Spandex (uses last cost from SAP material master, multiplies by actual usage)</li>
                        <li>System calculates NRV = Estimated Selling Price - Costs to Produce - Costs to Sell</li>
                        <li>System calculates Inventory Cost for EBITDA</li>
                        <li>System allocates Other VCC (uses plant-wise consumable costs, splits using merge factors for SKU-wise allocation)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Total VCC = Power + Heating + Antimony + Additives + Chemicals + Packing + Procured RM + NRV + Inventory Cost + Other VCC</li>
                        <li>System calculates Contribution = Gross Margin - Total VCC</li>
                        <li>System provides audit trails for all variable costs</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Alternate Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If material master rate is missing</li>
                        <li>System uses last available rate</li>
                        <li>System flags for user review</li>
                        <li>System sends notification</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Acceptance Criteria</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>All VCC components are calculated daily</li>
                        <li>SKU-level allocation is accurate</li>
                        <li>Audit trails are maintained</li>
                        <li>Power calculation uses correct plant factors</li>
                        <li>BOM mapping works for all materials</li>
                        <li>Contribution margin is calculated correctly</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody></table>

        <h3>2.4 Fixed Cost Conversion Module</h3>
        <table class="use-case-table">
            <tbody><tr>
                <td>Use Case ID</td>
                <td>UC-004</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Use Case Name</td>
                <td>Calculate Fixed Costs and Margin at Jolwa</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Primary Actor</td>
                <td>System (Automated) / HR/Admin User (Manual Entry)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Pre-Conditions</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Merge factors are configured</li>
                        <li>Production distribution logic is defined</li>
                        <li>Payroll data is available</li>
                        <li>Contract manpower data is available from IGMS and SAP</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Basic Process Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>System retrieves Stores &amp; Repairs data from SAP</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Manpower Payroll (Manual entry) with adjustment for leaves and overtime</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Contract Manpower from IGMS + SAP</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Insurance data (Manual entry) using Option 1 (Upfront allocation per planned sales quantity) or Option 2 (Daily spread using recurring monthly journals)</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Overheads (Manual/historical entry)</li>
                        <li>System allocates fixed costs to SKUs using merge factors and production distribution logic</li>
                        <li>System calculates Total Fixed Cost Conversion = Stores &amp; Repairs + Manpower Payroll + Contract Manpower + Insurance + Overheads</li>
                        <li>System retrieves Internal Shifting Cost of SFG (uses COGM, accounts for opening stock from SAP, maintains weighted average COGS daily)</li>
                        <li>System calculates Margin at Jolwa = Contribution - Total Fixed Cost Conversion - Internal Shifting Cost of SFG</li>
                        <li>System provides daily control and transparency</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Alternate Flow</td>
                <td>
                    <ol>
                        <li>If IGMS data is unavailable</li>
                        <li>System uses SAP contract manpower data only</li>
                        <li>System sends notification</li>
                        <li>User must verify and reconcile later</li>
                    </ol>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Acceptance Criteria</td>
                <td>
                    <ul>
                        <li>All fixed cost components are captured</li>
                        <li>SKU allocation uses correct merge factors</li>
                        <li>Payroll adjustments work correctly</li>
                        <li>Insurance allocation follows chosen method</li>
                        <li>Internal shifting costs are accurate</li>
                        <li>Margin at Jolwa is calculated correctly</li>
                        <li>Jolwa plant profitability is trackable</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody></table>

